29.xml"}, "text": "According to the case law of the BFH in the judgment of February 6, 1976 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "412) it is assumed that the shares in the general partner GmbH of the spouses to be assessed together for wealth tax serve the purposes of the limited partnership"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "As can be seen with reference to the BFH judgment of 18 December 1970 (BStBl 1971 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "289) results from Section 15 Paragraph 2 Sentence 1 VStR, the property of the spouse of a co-entrepreneur serving the business is to be treated like the property of the co-entrepreneur"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Since in the present case the spouses are assessed jointly for wealth tax, the GmbH shares of the wives of the limited partners of the KG are to be added to the business assets of this company"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Regarding question 1 b) (Gie\u00dfen tax office): In the event that only the wives of the limited partners are shareholders of the general partner GmbH, the same procedure should be followed as in question a)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "This handling can be defended with the corresponding application of the administrative instructions in Section 5 Paragraph 2 Sentences 1 and 2 VStR"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Re question 2 (Limburg tax office): The property that the spouses jointly own, which is more than 50 per cent"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "serves the operation of a partnership, in which only one of the two spouses is involved, is to be treated as business property of the partnership if, as can be seen from the facts, the requirements of \u00a7 26 No. 1 i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "V with Section 119 (1) BewG are available"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "This unequivocal conclusion is based on the BFH judgment of October 29, 1973 (BStBl 1974 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "79) to draw"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Agenda item III / 14 Increased tax exemption in accordance with Section 6 (4) VStG for a permanently disabled child in the case of joint assessment In the judgment of 12 10 1979 - III R 24/79 - (BStBl 1980 II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "166) the opinion of the tax court Rhineland-Palatinate from 20 11 1978 (EFG 1979 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "207) confirms that a child who is permanently disabled is to be granted a tax-free amount in accordance with Section 6 (4) VStG, regardless of the total assets of the collective investment scheme, if the child's assets do not exceed DM 150,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "The opinion represented in this decision is not to be brought into line with the administrative instruction contained in section 121, paragraph 2, sentence 5 VStR, according to which the child's assets must also be taken into account when calculating the asset limit of 150,000 DM or 300,000 DM if parents or a Parent can be assessed together with a child"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "According to the HMdF decree of 20 6 1980 - S-3522 A - 2 - II B 43 - (announced by Rdvfg"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "from 29 7 1980 - VSt-Kartei 1980 \u00a7 6 VStG card 2) is according to the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Judgment to proceed without restriction"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "The arrangement of Section 121 (2), last sentence of the VStR, which contradicts this legal interpretation, is replaced by the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "BFH judgment outdated"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In addition, in the judgment of 25 January 1980 (BStBl II p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "262) in a similar case not only confirms his previous view of the asset limit, but also expressly decided that a child is a \"taxpayer\" within the meaning of the VStG and also unable to work i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 6 Paragraph 4 No. 1 VStG, even if it could not pursue an acquisition according to its age"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Regarding the facts: Taking into account the above"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Explanation is for the mentally handicapped and constantly helpless daughter, with whom the taxpayer upon application according to \u00a7 14 Abs 2 Nr 2 VStG i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "V is assessed together with Section 125 c Paragraph 1 Clause 3 VStR, an allowance due to incapacity for work in accordance with"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Section 6 (4) VStG if the subsidiary's assets do not exceed DM 150,000 and the subsidiary's tax-free claims under Section 111 Nos. 1 to 4 and 9 BewG do not exceed DM 4,800 per year"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "If the tax-exempt claims are more than DM 4800, an allowance is to be granted in accordance with Section 6 (3) VStG, provided the (total) assets of the daughter do not exceed DM 150,000"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Agenda item III / 15 To what extent should \"higher-income taxpayers\" investigate the complete recording of other assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 1 - 3 VStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "The fullest possible record of all persons to be assessed for wealth tax must be made in compliance with the circular dated 11 9 1979 S-3543 A - 1 - St III 42 contained in the wealth tax card index (General - Card 7)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Accordingly, in the course of income tax assessments, all taxpayers who declare income from capital assets of more than DM 15,000 and / or a total amount of income of more than DM 250,000 must be sent a wealth tax return and continuously checked whether the assets shown in the tax files are those according to the valuation law and the wealth tax law exceeds the allowances to be taken into account, and in the appropriate cases to submit a wealth tax return"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the HZD has been commissioned by the HMdF to issue test note 546"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In addition, however, there are all indications arising from the tax files that refer to assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 1 - 3 BewG, to take the opportunity to consult the taxpayers in the course of carrying out the wealth tax assessments if the existing wealth tax declarations do not provide sufficient information"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Such indications may exist as a result of the acquisition or sale of real estate"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In such cases, it is advisable to follow the instructions in the \"Guidelines for Investigations, Checks and Complaints in the VTB\" after S"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "38 printed forms 1 to 4 are to be used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "From the amount of income from capital assets, conclusions can be drawn about the possible amount of the value of assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 1 - 3 are drawn"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In particular, it will also be the task of the tax audit to investigate the existence of such assets and their value based on the movements of withdrawals and deposits from traders and freelancers"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Agenda item III / 16 To what extent should \"higher-income taxpayers\" have other assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 10-12 VStG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In the case of higher-income taxpayers - taxpayers who declare a total income of more than DM 250,000 can be regarded as such - it can generally be assumed that they are the owners of economic goods in the sense of"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 10 - 12 BewG"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "The same can be assumed for wealthy millionaires - regardless of the level of their income"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In such cases it seems appropriate to search for assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 10 - 12 BewG if the present wealth tax returns contain no information on this"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "If there is a presumption that the taxpayers have not fully stated their assets of this type, a consultation with the taxpayers generally only promises success if the tax files give evidence that suggests the acquisition of such assets"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "That would be"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "the case when previously declared capital stocks (capital claims, credit balances, securities) are no longer shown in the wealth tax returns and the tax files do not provide any information about the purposes for which these assets have been used"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In these cases, the taxpayers can be expected to provide proof of use"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "On luxury items within the meaning of Section 110 (1) No. 11 BewG, u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "be closed if taxpayers only have negative income from certain properties"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "That would be"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "the case when a thoroughbred breed is maintained and a hobby business has been accepted for income tax purposes (see BFH judgment - BStBl 1960 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "324 and 64 p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "79) or a breeding and racing stable is operated as a hobby (see BFH - BStBl 1964 III p"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "In such cases, u"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "economic goods according to Section 110 (1) No. 8 BewG may also be given"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "Riding horses that are kept for sporting reasons, on the other hand, are to be treated like gliders and sailing boats (usually economic goods within the meaning of Section 111 No. 10 BewG)"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "It must also be the task of the tax auditor to determine the existence of assets i"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "of \u00a7 110 Paragraph 1 No. 10-12 to conduct investigations"}, {"meta": {"name": "0057729.xml"}, "text": "--- Accounting, valuation, inheritance and gift tax, Hesse, BewG, VStG"}]